What:		/sys/bus/i2c/devices/[0-9]+-0078/detect/enable
Date:		June 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6
Contact:	"Jim Wylder" <jwylder@google.com>
Description:
	Enable/Disable water detection.  0 = disabled, 1 = enabled.  (RW)
	To function both detect/enable and at least once sensor/enable
	must be set to 1.  Once the fuse is blow ('open'), it will remain
	in that condition.

What:		/sys/bus/i2c/devices/[0-9]+-0078/detect/mode
Date:		June 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6
Contact:	"Jim Wylder" <jwylder@google.com>
Description:
	Detection runs in two modes 'wet' and 'dry'.  The system typically
	runs to detect water intrusion ('wet').  In this case the notification
	will be given when the sensor transitions from a not detecting water
	to detecting water.  Alternately, setting the mode 'dry' after water
	has been detected, will signal when the sensor has dried.

What:		/sys/bus/i2c/devices/[0-9]+-0078/fuse/enable
Date:		June 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6
Contact:	"Jim Wylder" <jwylder@google.com>
Description:
