What:		/sys/bus/i2c/devices/[0-9]+-0078/sensor[0-2]/boot_value
Date:		Oct 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6
Contact:	"Jim Wylder" <jwylder@google.com>
Description:
	Show value read into memory during boot.  Provides same function as
	latched_value, but reflects any state changes that may have occurred
	while the phone was off, or not fully booted. Return values are:
	'wet' = sensor detects water,
	'dry' = sensor does not detect water,
	'dis' = sensor is not enabled (detect/enable != 1 or sensor/enable != 1)
	'inv' = sensor reading is invalid, because the reference sensor is 'wet'.

What:		/sys/bus/i2c/devices/[0-9]+-0078/sensor[0-2]/latched_value
Date:		June 2024
KernelVersion:	6.6
Contact:	"Jim Wylder" <jwylder@google.com>
Description:
	Show value read into memory from interrupt handler.  Return values are:
	'wet' = sensor detects water,
	'dry' = sensor does not detect water,
	'dis' = sensor is not enabled (detect/enable != 1 or sensor/enable != 1)
	'inv' = sensor reading is invalid, because the reference sensor is 'wet'.

